.TH "shcrosspowerdensityl" "1" "2021-02-15" "Fortran 95" "SHTOOLS 4.12"
.hy
.SH SHCrossPowerDensityL
.PP
Compute the cross-power spectral density of two real functions for a
single spherical harmonic degree.
.SH Usage
.PP
\f[V]cpsd\f[R] = SHCrossPowerDensityL (\f[V]cilm1\f[R], \f[V]cilm2\f[R],
\f[V]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[V]cpsd\f[R] : output, real(dp)
Cross-power spectral density of the two real functions for spherical
harmonic degree \f[V]l\f[R].
.TP
\f[V]cilm1\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[V]lmaxin1\f[R]+1, \f[V]lmaxin1\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the first real function.
.TP
\f[V]cilm2\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[V]lmaxin2\f[R]+1, \f[V]lmaxin2\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the second real function.
.TP
\f[V]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to the minimum of \f[V]lmaxin1\f[R] and
\f[V]lmaxin2\f[R].
.SH Description
.PP
\f[V]SHCrossPowerDensityL\f[R] will calculate the cross-power spectral
density of two real functions expressed in real 4-pi normalized
spherical harmonics for a single spherical harmonic degree \f[V]l\f[R].
This is explicitly calculated as:
.PP
\f[V]cpsd = Sum_{i=1}\[ha]2 Sum_{m=0}\[ha]l cilm1(i, l+1, m+1) * cilm2(i, l+1, m+1) / (2l + 1)\f[R].
